<section class="page-hero reveal">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      How ImperialPaws Pekingese handles adoption inquiries, applications, tracking, and invoice details.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-content reveal">
  <div class="container narrow reveal">
    <p>
      ImperialPaws Pekingese collects only the information needed to review adoption
      applications, communicate with prospective families, manage application
      tracking, moderate testimonials, and prepare adoption invoices for approved
      buyers.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      Application forms may ask for your name, email address, phone number,
      location, message, and the puppy you are applying for. Approved invoices may
      include buyer contact details and agreed adoption fee information.
    </p>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>
      Information is used to review placement suitability, contact applicants,
      update application status, prepare invoices, protect against duplicate
      applications, and maintain accurate adoption records.
    </p>

    <h2>Payments and Invoices</h2>
    <p>
      No public website visitor is asked to pay before application review and
      approval. Invoice links are intended for approved buyers and should be kept
      private.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Storage</h2>
    <p>
      The website may store application, puppy, testimonial, and invoice records
      using configured database storage and may store puppy images using configured
      image storage. Access to admin tools is restricted to authorized users.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about privacy or adoption records may be sent through the contact
      information listed on the contact page when available.
    </p>

    <p class="closing-note">
      Last updated: <%= new Date().getFullYear() %>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
